items.title: 'We all know someone who was killed' -  Iran protesters tell BBC of brutal crackdown
items.description: Young Iranians able tell the BBC how they saw friends and other people die as security forces crushed protests earlier this month.

items.title: TikTok US pushes back on claims it is censoring content
items.description: Thousands of people claim political content is being suppressed after the US operation was spun off.

items.title: Families sue US over deadly boat strike off Venezuela coast
items.description: Relatives of Chad Joseph and Rishi Samaroo - among six killed on 14 October - say the Trinidadian men were returning home when their vessel was hit.

items.title: US to send ICE agents to Winter Olympics, prompting Italian anger
items.description: The US federal agency says it will not play an immigration role at February's event in Milan-Cortina.

items.title: TikTok settles just before social media addiction trial to begin
items.description: Defendants include Meta, which owns Instagram and Facebook, and YouTube parent Google.
